Coloration variation. In life, lateral edge of body and venter with orange streak in males, becoming less distinct at midbody towards back leg (
Figs. 5–6
). A male paratype ( USNM 346561 ) was elsewhere described in life as having an orange-colored side with cream spotting below the lateral line (
McCranie & Wilson 2001
). This orange streak is not apparent in preservative. A pattern-less morph occurred in both males and females. One male ( MZFC 24831 ) had some dark mottling on chin.
